Durban - Bathers have been warned to adhere to lifeguard instructions as sharks nets have been removed along the KwaZulu-Natal coast. 
This, as employees of the KZN Sharks Board are set to embark on a strike on Friday. 
The Board said in a statement that the shark safety gear was being removed from protected beaches temporarily to minimise the environmental impact, however, the duration of the strike was unknown.
