Negotiations on wages and other worker demands have between Board management and the South African Liberating Public Sector Workers Union (Salipswu) have been going on since December last year. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
“The matter has been heard at the CCMA on a number of occasions unfortunately without resolution,” read the statement. 
Bathers were cautioned to adhere to lifeguard instructions and recommendations for their safety while the Board continues to negotiate with the union.
